<i>Come, children. </i>

48
00:03:36,787 --> 00:03:39,654
You hear me, Sarah Jane?
Hot dogs!

49
00:03:39,724 --> 00:03:44,627
Oh, boy!
Come on! Boy!
Hot dogs!

50
00:03:44,695 --> 00:03:50,327
It might be the noise of
that old ocean, but it seems
to me I didn't hear thank you.

51
00:03:50,401 --> 00:03:52,926
I was too hungry.
Thank <i>you</i>!
Thank <i>you</i>!

52
00:03:53,004 --> 00:03:55,097
Honey, you gonna be all right.
I reported you.

53
00:03:55,173 --> 00:03:57,801
Come on, Sarah Jane!
No, you're gonna stay
right here.

54
00:03:57,875 --> 00:04:00,605
[Together]
Oh!
Else how
your mama gonna find you?

55
00:04:00,678 --> 00:04:04,136
<i>Susie! Oh, Susie! </i>

56
00:04:04,215 --> 00:04:07,878
Oh, my baby! Oh,
I thought you were lost.

57
00:04:07,952 --> 00:04:10,284
Thank you, Officer.
Thank you very much.

58
00:04:10,354 --> 00:04:13,755
And thank you for being
so kind, Mrs... .
Johnson.

59
00:04:13,824 --> 00:04:17,555
I'm Lora Meredith.
I've never been
so frightened in my life.

60
00:04:17,628 --> 00:04:20,893
One moment I had her,
and the next moment
she was gone.

61
00:04:20,965 --> 00:04:23,900
Thank Mrs. Johnson
for being so nice.
Thank you!

62
00:04:23,968 --> 00:04:27,199
And say good-bye
to the little girl.
Good-bye? Now?

63
00:04:27,271 --> 00:04:30,672
But, darling, we have
to go back to the city.
But we wanna play!

64
00:04:30,741 --> 00:04:32,971
Please?
Please, Mommy,
please!

65
00:04:33,044 --> 00:04:36,207
Oh, all right.
But only for a little while.

66
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:39,340
[Squealing]
Come on, Sarah Jane!

67
00:04:39,417 --> 00:04:41,408
You're it!
<i>You're it! </i>

68
00:04:41,485 --> 00:04:44,454
You're it!
You're it!

69
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:49,618
Susie doesn't have many
children to play with
where we live.

70
00:04:49,694 --> 00:04:53,061
I guess Sarah Jane's
kind of lonesome too.

71
00:04:53,130 --> 00:04:55,690
They got along fine
right off.

72
00:04:55,766 --> 00:04:59,702
Sarah Jane's a lovely child.
How long have you
taken care of her?

73
00:04:59,770 --> 00:05:01,931
All her life.

74
00:05:02,006 --> 00:05:04,440
Oh, I wish I had someone
to look after Susie.

75
00:05:04,508 --> 00:05:08,706
A maid to live in?
Someone to take care
of your little girl?

76
00:05:08,779 --> 00:05:11,179
A strong, healthy,
settled-down woman...

77
00:05:11,249 --> 00:05:14,184
who eats like a bird
and doesn't care
if she gets no time off...

78
00:05:14,252 --> 00:05:16,345
and will work real cheap?

79
00:05:16,420 --> 00:05:19,548
Well, yes, if one exists.
Oh, someday.

80
00:05:19,624 --> 00:05:22,650
Why not today?
I'm available.

81
00:05:22,727 --> 00:05:25,491
You?
Me. Annie Johnson.

82
00:05:25,563 --> 00:05:29,158
You mean you'd
consider leaving that
lovely little girl?

83
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:32,795
Oh, I wouldn't be leaving her.
My baby goes where I go.

84
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:36,033
<i>[Children Chattering]</i>

85
00:05:36,107 --> 00:05:38,837
Sarah Jane
is <i>your</i> child?

86
00:05:38,909 --> 00:05:42,276
Yes, ma'am.
It surprises most people.

87
00:05:42,346 --> 00:05:45,975
Sarah Jane favors her daddy.
He was practically white.

88
00:05:46,050 --> 00:05:48,541
He left before she was born.

89
00:05:48,619 --> 00:05:52,146
Seems to me, Miss Meredith,
I'm just right for you.

90
00:05:52,223 --> 00:05:56,182
You wouldn't have to pay
no wages. Just let me come
and do for you.

91
00:05:56,260 --> 00:06:01,755
I couldn't do that.
I'd have to pay you,
and I... can't now.

92
00:06:01,832 --> 00:06:04,198
[Snoring]

93
00:06:04,268 --> 00:06:05,599
Susie!

94
00:06:05,670 --> 00:06:07,262
[Snoring]

95
00:06:07,338 --> 00:06:10,466
[Laughing]
[Laughing]

96
00:06:10,541 --> 00:06:13,237
I ought to knock
your blocks off.

97
00:06:13,311 --> 00:06:16,246
I'll take care of it,
mister. I'll wham
the hides off both of them.

98
00:06:16,314 --> 00:06:19,442
<i>Susie! What are</i>
<i>you doing? </i>
About time you showed up!

99
00:06:19,517 --> 00:06:21,485
<i>If your husband can't keep</i>
<i>these brats in line... </i>

100
00:06:21,552 --> 00:06:25,488
No use talking to her.
She not only spoils them,
she goes around losing them.

101
00:06:25,556 --> 00:06:27,524
I don't know what
this is all about.

102
00:06:27,591 --> 00:06:31,550
Mommy, look at his stomach.
It went up and down.
It was so funny.

103
00:06:31,629 --> 00:06:33,790
He took our picture.
Will you send me one?

104
00:06:33,864 --> 00:06:35,798
Me too.
Sure. Where?

105
00:06:35,866 --> 00:06:39,962
<i>Send it to Susan Meredith, </i>
<i>450 Prescott Place, </i>
<i>Apartment 3 2.</i>

106
00:06:40,037 --> 00:06:42,301
Never mind, dear.
See? I remembered.

107
00:06:42,373 --> 00:06:45,638
Thank you.
And send her one too.
Where do you live, Sarah Jane?

108
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:50,113
Where do I live...
No place.

109
00:06:50,181 --> 00:06:52,979
We'll find a place
come night, honey.

110
00:06:53,050 --> 00:06:56,178
Come on, darling, we have
to go. Say good-bye to
Sarah Jane and Mrs. Johnson.

111
00:06:56,253 --> 00:06:58,881
Good-bye.
It was very nice
meeting you.

112
00:06:58,956 --> 00:07:01,891
Same here.
And good luck,
Miss Meredith.

113
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:05,486
Mommy, I'm tired.
I know, baby.

114
00:07:05,563 --> 00:07:09,158
<i>I know. </i>
<i>I wanna go home too! </i>

115
00:07:09,233 --> 00:07:12,031
Come on, honey.

116
00:07:12,103 --> 00:07:14,628
Thank you.
<i>Mrs. Johnson. </i>

117
00:07:16,006 --> 00:07:18,839
Oh. Oh, come on.

118
00:07:24,248 --> 00:07:26,307
[Girls Giggling]

119
