I don't like
to mention it again, but
you must understand that...

122
00:07:41,365 --> 00:07:43,299
this arrangement
can only be for tonight.
<i>[Door Slamming]</i>

123
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:45,494
Oh, I understand,
Miss Lora.

124
00:07:45,569 --> 00:07:47,503
There must be plenty of jobs
for a woman like you.

125
00:07:47,571 --> 00:07:49,801
But people won't take in
a woman with a child.

126
00:07:49,874 --> 00:07:53,037
And no matter what, I won't
be separated from my baby.

127
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:55,635
Hurry up, Mother.
I want to show Sarah Jane
my dolls!

128
00:07:55,713 --> 00:07:57,647
Well, all right.

129
00:08:08,526 --> 00:08:10,892
There's a little place
off the kitchen.

130
00:08:13,364 --> 00:08:16,492
But you could, uh,
hardly call it a room.

131
00:08:19,136 --> 00:08:22,970
Oh, it'll do
for Sarah Jane and me.

132
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:27,374
And the kitchen,
we can make use of that too.

133
00:08:27,445 --> 00:08:31,245
I'll get you some
pillows and blankets.
Thank you.

134
00:08:36,487 --> 00:08:39,251
Here, Sarah Jane,
you can have Nancy.

135
00:08:41,659 --> 00:08:46,961
It's a present.
Mommy just got it for me.
I want that one.

136
00:08:47,031 --> 00:08:51,297
Frieda's my friend.
I've had her all my life.

137
00:08:51,368 --> 00:08:55,327
Mommy!
Mommy!
<i>Yes? </i>

138
00:08:55,406 --> 00:08:58,034
She took my doll!
Oh.

139
00:08:58,108 --> 00:09:02,340
<i>Sarah Jane. </i>
<i>Where are your manners? </i>
<i>Now give it back. </i>

140
00:09:02,413 --> 00:09:05,007
I don't want the black one.
I'll take those.

141
00:09:05,082 --> 00:09:07,141
It's been a long day
and they're both tired
and cranky.

142
00:09:07,218 --> 00:09:09,516
Yes, Miss Lora.
Everything will be all right.

143
00:09:09,587 --> 00:09:11,521
Come on, come on.
[Sarah Jane Crying]

144
